title.narrative: WOS COORDINATION

description.narrative: UNICEF coordination of the sectors at the Whole of Syria and the hub levels is managed efficiently and effectively, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Operations Support To Programme Delivery (Covid), Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: MENARO delivers timely, equitable and principled humanitarian action as a complement to country office-led operations where required, including through the cross-border component of the Syria programmes as part of the Whole of Syria response.

title.narrative: UNICEF coordination of the sectors at the Whole of Syria and the hub levels is managed efficiently and effectively

description.narrative: During 2021, UNICEF has maintained Whole of Syria and NWS Hub (Gaziantep) coordination capacity. UNICEF has continued to support effective sector coordination for WASH, Nutrition, Education and Child Protection (Area of Responsibility) in WoS and programmes in NWS. UNICEF has invested in coordination and to develop capacities of the different humanitarian stakeholders and leveraged its resources to address humanitarian needs. Throughout all the year, UNICEF has used its cluster lead obligations and its strategic engagement at several levels,;to promote its values related to equity, gender and protection of rights. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:27/01/2022
